 If this temperature differential increases, what will happen? 

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:09.520
 By the way of logic we understand that if this is super hot here, 

00:03:09.520 --> 00:03:12.920
 it's much hotter than the right, 

00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:15.320
 then more heat will be transferred. 

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:19.040
 You will have more heat transferred per unit of time, 

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:22.880
 then the heat transfer rate will increase. 

00:03:22.880 --> 00:03:25.440
 Similarly, if this difference decreases - 

00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:26.920
 and you can take the extreme case - 

00:03:26.920 --> 00:03:28.620
 if there is no difference - 

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:31.550
 if T with index a was the same as T with index b, 

00:03:31.550 --> 00:03:36.020
 then you will not have heat transfer in any time unit. 

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:38.240
 It is logical that the heat transfer rate 

00:03:38.240 --> 00:03:42.050
 will be proportional to the temperature difference. 

00:03:42.050 --> 00:03:44.680
 How can we gather all these logical reasoning 

00:03:44.680 --> 00:03:48.620
 in a formula to describe the thermal conductivity, 

00:03:48.620 --> 00:03:53.860
 to think how quickly this heat will be transferred, 

00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:56.340
 the heat transfer rate? 

