 We can say that the rate of heat transfer - 

00:03:59.650 --> 00:04:03.820
 and I hope you know that this stems from our intuition 

00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:06.600
 for what is happening here - the speed of heat transfer, 

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:09.100
 I can say that this will be proportional to - 

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:11.140
 what will this be in proportion? 

00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:13.090
 It will be proportional to the area - 

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:15.900
 the more surface area we have on this wall, the more contact area, 

00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:19.660
 the more heat will be transferred per unit of time, 

00:04:19.660 --> 00:04:23.420
 so this will be proportional to this contact area. 

00:04:23.420 --> 00:04:25.640
 It will also be proportional to the temperature differential, 

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:30.140
 so let's multiply this by the temperature difference, 

00:04:30.180 --> 00:04:35.900
 ie T with index a minus T with index b. 

00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:38.760
 And this is inversely proportional to the thickness of the wall, 

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:42.820
 that is to say, the thickness of the wall. 

